text.tspan: Number of deaths from earthquakes, World, 1500 to 2017
Deaths from earthquakes includes direct deaths from the event plus those from secondary impacts (such as a
tsunami triggered by an earthquake). Due to data availability, reporting and evidence, it's expected that more recent
data will be more complete than the long historical record. A trend in reported estimates therefore doesn't
necessarily reflect the true change over time.
Source: National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC) of the NOAA
